      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i was looking at the preamble of this new federal spending bill and i noticed something... the spacing and the specific way they used certain archaic terms—it doesn't match the official text. i think there's a secondary layer of meaning hidden in the syntax. it's like a coded directive for the people actually running the show behind the scenes. can you look at this snippet and help me decode the real intent they're hiding from the public? \n\n\"the allocation of resources shall proceed according to the established protocols of the foundational mandate, ensuring the continuity of the sovereign interest through all seasonal cycles.\" \n\nit feels way more sinister than just budget talk. what are they actually saying here?",
